biolockj.module.implicit.parser

Interface ParserModule

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BioModule, JavaModule, ScriptModule
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    KrakenParser, MetaphlanParser, ParserModuleImpl, QiimeParser, RdpParser, SlimmParser

    public interface ParserModule
extends JavaModule
    This interface defines the required methods to parse ClassifierModule output. Each BioLockJ ClassifierModule implementation must have a corresponding ParserModule that understands the classifier output file format to extract the OTU counts assigned to each sample. Parser BioModules read ClassifierModule output to build standardized OTU abundance tables.

    • Method Detail

      • addParsedSample

        void addParsedSample(ParsedSample parsedSample)
              throws Exception
        Each sample with taxonomic assignments from a ClassifierModule is parsed by parseSamples() to produce a ParsedSample. As each file is processed, this method is called to add the ParsedSample to the Set returned by getParsedSamples()
        Parameters:
        parsedSample - ParsedSample
        Throws:
        Exception - if unable to add the parsed sample

      • buildOtuTables

        void buildOtuTables()
             throws Exception
        After parseSamples() completes, this method builds the OTU tables. For each level in Config."report.taxonomyLevels", 1 OTU table is generated.
        Throws:
        Exception - if error occurs while building OTU tables

      • getParsedSample
